{#-
name: never-assume-tests-pass
summary: Always run a test you just wrote or modified — never assume it passes.
domain: engineering
audience: agent
severity: default
-#}
**Never assume a test passes.** After writing or modifying a test, run it yourself. Self-reported "should pass" without a run is how regressions land in `main`.

```sh
uv run --group test pytest tests/unit/test_<name>.py -s
```
